got to sql congigeration manager > sql server network configuration > Protocols > TCP/IP Enable
after got property of TCP/IP > Click IPAddresses Tab > IPAll > ipaddress set to blank and port must be 1433
After that 
Open Sql Server
Right Click on Server instance and go to properties>Security>Sql server window Authontication mode enable
Got to Connect in property Enable Allow Remote Connection to server
After That Click on Instance
and click on security > Login> Right Click New Login > Login Name Xyz > Enable Sql server Authentication > Set password > Enforce password Policy enable
add port in allow incoming connection 
